StandingBalanceEval
author dmm
status proposed

In the StandingBalanceEval model, the question is "What is the patient's standing balance?" and the coded answers can be 'Requires support','Does not stand', and 'Stable at bedside' etc.

LOINC code for this eval looks like 45610-3 Balance while standing [Minimum Data Set]
LOINC data values (shared with Sitting Balance):
   Maintained position as required in test
   Unsteady, but able to rebalance self without physical support
   Partial physical support during test; or stands (sits) but does not follow directions for test
   Not able to attempt test without physical help

